sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>Controller
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>Training Worker
    participant Worker as Worker Pod(s)<br/>Training Workers
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>DNS Discovery
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Worker: Flow 1: Distributed PyTorch Training Job Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob created

    Note over Operator: Watch event triggers reconciliation

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup (if gang scheduling)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod + env vars<br/>(MASTER_ADDR, WORLD_SIZE, RANK=0)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods + env vars<br/>(MASTER_ADDR, WORLD_SIZE, RANK=N)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Services<br/>(per-pod DNS discovery)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>(PyTorch only)

    K8sAPI-->>Master: Pod scheduled
    K8sAPI-->>Worker: Pods scheduled
    K8sAPI-->>HeadlessSvc: Service created

    Note over Worker,Master: Init containers wait for Master DNS resolution

    Worker->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup for master<br/>53/TCP+UDP, No encryption
    HeadlessSvc-->>Worker: Master pod IP

    Note over Worker,Master: Distributed training begins

    Worker->>Master: Connect for training<br/>23456/TCP PyTorch NCCL/Gloo<br/>No encryption
    Worker->>Worker: Peer-to-peer gradients<br/>23456/TCP PyTorch NCCL/Gloo<br/>No encryption

    Note over Operator: Status reconciliation loop

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch Pod status changes
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>(Running/Succeeded/Failed)

    Prometheus->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>No auth

    Note over User,Worker: Flow 2: MPI Job with Launcher/Worker Architecture

    User->>K8sAPI: POST MPIJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: MPIJob created

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap<br/>(hostfile + kubexec.sh scripts)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>+ Role + RoleBinding<br/>(pod exec permissions for launcher)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods
    K8sAPI-->>Worker: Worker pods scheduled

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Launcher Pod<br/>(with kubectl-delivery init container)

    Note over Master: Launcher pod = "Master" in MPI topology

    Master->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec into Workers<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Launcher ServiceAccount token
    Worker->>Worker: MPI communication<br/>9999/TCP MPI protocol<br/>No encryption
